Okay! 

Recently I read this amazing article on ‘How the Ancient Art of Making Tea Became Modern Self-Care.’ 

- (A 2000 year old practice of meditation reveals the blessings of slowing down, waking up and smelling the matcha) 

What I took away from the read and now add to some form of my daily routine is the delicate art of doing something slowly with intention that can’t be repeated the same way. The pouring, steeping, stirring, waiting, it’s all a practice of Patience that I’ve been getting better at.

Tea can definitely be a TEAchable moment each day 🤌🏾

-PS grapefruits are life!
Color your world! 💋✌🏾

THE ART OF GIVING AND RECEIVING - (this duality can exist)

I always admire people who are great teachers and learners, great partners who can lead but still be lead or compromise and fantastic speakers who can stop and listen when needed.

I’m slowly stepping into a space where I feel comfortable watching others create on me and I create with them.

Here’s 24 hrs of dancing and moving. Saturday to Sunday.
You know Monday definitely HAS to be a rest day lol 

And fam two things such as giving and receiving can co exist in the same space.

The Art of Receiving Cont’d (see previous post) ➡️

So this morning my cousin was very creative and detailed in creating this butterfly effect in my hair and I absolutely love this feminine exchange. Another light bulb moment to just let her do her thing and be her muse. Yup that’s receiving. 

BUTTERFLY OMEN is a powerful beacon of growth and new beginnings, the butterfly signifies the power of transformation and the incredible feats we can achieve when we trust ourselves. We all have the ability to listen to our innate wisdom, guide ourselves through difficult times, and emerge better and stronger than before.

Thanks for doing your crazy creative, detailed oriented ideas on me @rotchelleparris 

Dress by: @pinklemonadebyrp 🥰

WHY ATTENTION ISN’T INTENTION💋

I think talking about the neuroscience behind FLIRTING is a great way to understand the biologically wired feeling of loving attention when someone likes a pic, slide into your dms, shows you a short burst of care or even interest. 

But the real question is does this dopamine hit really matter if it doesn’t have a defined or pure intention behind it?

I guess tomorrow is that day where most of you will be looking for that extra attention and love from a significant other or your little sneaky link but always remember good INTENTION matters more.

Remember you don’t need a specific day to show your love and great intentions for the people you love in your life 💋

Dress by : @pinklemonadebyrp

HOW THE TREES TAUGHT ME A LESSON IN LETTING GO.

I think what I love so much about the outdoors and nature is observing the trees and how they are so effortlessly forgiving of the seasons we go/ grow through yearly. 

We live in the Caribbean obviously and though the seasons may not be as drastic change still occurs.

What the trees have taught me is this ACCEPTANCE and BRAVERY of shedding its leaves knowing that when it’s season is time to bloom again there is TRUST that it will definitely come. The trust in the nothingness knowing something better and more aligned will always come 💚✨

What are you willing to let go?

Inspired by @wholeheartedcoaching 💚

HOW ARE YOU SHOWERING YOURSELF WITH THE BLESSINGS YOU DESRVE TODAY?

I think I’m a pro now at taking myself out to random art galleries, movies on a Sunday, drives on the East cost of Bim or just a quiet beach day. I told y’all it’s my Emily in Paris year and I really mean it. 

The aim is to spoil my damn self knowing that when the next person comes along Im not easily surprised or wowed by the minimum. (It’s always good to start small first though lol)

Y’all better LIKE YA SELF as Machel say.

A LOVE LETTER TO ALL MY DANCE TEACHERS WHEN I WAS YOUNGER. 

Dear Teacher, 

Thank you for teaching me that the highest form of ART is not the appreciation of others but the lasting of my soul. 

Thank you for giving me the convenience that I have today to wear anything without shame because some of those costumes were always questionable to wear in public 

Thank you for showing me different way to EMOTE on and off stage that now these are some mental tools I can use in my relationships.

Thank you for teaching me MATH like no other way with all the counting, timing and rhythms that maybe hard at times

Thank you for drilling DISCIPLINE and TIME MANAGEMENT cause those call times, long rehearsals aren’t easy.

Thank you for pushing me when no one else will. 

-A forever student of Dance.

The Theme is Treat Yo’ Self!

Last week in my stretch class I was teaching a short quick psychology exercise I learned back at school in expressing gratitude and comparing what you were grateful for at 10 years old versus your present self.

Immediately thought about my 10 year self and being grateful for the ice-cream truck to pull up in my childhood gap with a guaranteed FREE ice cream Lolly ! Ha ! Such a core memory 

Now most times as adults we think about the bigger things to be grateful for like cars, travels, money, paid bills. 

As we move through life what we’re grateful for moves away from the small but great simple things in life like Ice Cream and moves to the bigger elements. 

Don’t forget to treat yo’ self! And be grateful for the small sweet things in life ✨💙🤍

@ilovefrosteez @ilovechefette

EVERYONE LOVES AN UNDERDOG STORY!

Yes this post is about my man my man my man @michaelbjordan in Creed 3! @creedmovie 

Most times when we watch stories we root for the underdog because we see so much of ourselves in the characters played out in movies 

I was rooting for MBJ regardless but what I love about this film so much is that we both empathized with the protagonist AND the antagonist which made the film very real and genuine.

I say all this to say to create your own story, however that plays out. You may feel like you’re working towards something and it’s not getting anywhere or you may see people passing you out in the race or maybe you’re in your own lane.

Remember YOU are the underdog with the consistency and practice at the craft you love.

I’m not saying be Michael B Jordan 😍😛but keep fighting! 

PS : I was here literally watching over the movie a 3rd time before my rehearsal  started🤣 #myman

Let me sip this tea over here and have a quickie chat on FRIENDSHIPS

Earlier a friend called to check in on me and I immediately felt this urge of guilt because of how busy I am most days and I haven’t been checking in in abit. She also has a lot going on and she took the time to just call and check in. Loved that.

This year my goal was to be more INTENTIONAL about my close relationships and friendships and if you know me you know how I feel about friends.

The older we get the more chaotic life seems and we pay so much more attention to Romantic relationships that we forget friendships are meaningful as well.

So that quick check in was a great reminder that friends really do matter and a little “hey crazy ass Meggz, what’s up?” Is always needed and vice versa

No one ever talks about living an intentional life as a SINGLE BAJAN GAL so I’ll share my experience.

We’re not going to talk about how ghetto these streets are but rather about how privileged the single people are in Barbados to have access to such peaceful spaces we can truly tap into our inner beauty while exploring our outer reality in peace and silence.

This is the first time since I was in secondary school where I am intentionally living that single life with the thought process of ACTIVELY WAITING (the juxtaposition honestly makes sense) trust me.

But what I’m really trying to say is we focus so much on dating, meeting new people, proving ourselves to someone, or waiting for the one when really and truly it’s kind of waste of time while the world is continuously revolving around us. The world is waiting for YOU! 

So DONT forget to actively wait and have the most fun and experiences you can while you can😘

Recently I’ve been deep in research on the feminine archetypes and realized as I get older I’ve slowly been moving through all 7.

The Huntress- Independent spirit & sexy, devil-may-care attitude is irresistible.

The Lover- You are unbridled and your erotic energy is in its purest, most tantalizing form.

The Mystic - Your sultry, serene presence makes you appear other worldly.

The Maiden- Your impish mix of girlish charm and mature sensuality enthralls others.

The Queen- Your regal presence and glamorous nature enchants us.

The Sage- You exude elegance, worldliness and a touch of mystery.

The Mother-  You are a fountain of love, affection and robust sensuality.

Dimitri Dump❤️

He was made for me! The excitement, exploration and enthusiasm for outside is real.

This week was the last week before I take a break from teaching and for most classes each week we move with a theme.

I realize that one of my students was breathing hard after each sequence of movements and I immediately realized she wasn’t being intentional about her BREATH; her inhale and exhale. 

So that’s the theme we ran with this week for class. Learning how to intentionally practice your inhale and exhale.

I use this juxtaposition in my personal life so much while I try to really focus on when to inhale take in all the information, rest, observe and focus and exhaling all the negative self talk, insecurities and stress that usually solitons me sometimes.

DONT FORGET TO BE INTENTIONAL ABOUT YOUR BREATH EACH DAY.

It definitely helps 💕

Updating my “This is her pics” 🤭

The ladies were in my dms all summer saying “This summer belongs to you” “this is your summer,” and that really got me to thinking.

As a long time performer/ dancer I spent alllllll my summers on stage performing, late nights into the morning rehearsing and not to mention dance internships and intensives  in studio for the entire season.

I truly never knew Crop Over from the lens of a patron, only as a performer. This season I said let’s put on a different lens and enjoy the season for what it truly is and boy oh boy I really REALLY did. I see why y’all be outside doing the most. 

This sense of liberation, freedom and enthusiasm for life has enlightened my soul for what’s coming next and I’m so excited!

THE FIRST BITE IS ALWAYS NOSTALGIC.

A few days ago I was really thinking deep (as I always do) what triggers NOSTALGIA?

Google answered: 
Familiar music, smells, and other reminders of the past activate nostalgic feelings. Nostalgia is often triggered by sensory stimuli, but it can be elicited by conversations, and even by self-directed memory recollection.

I immediately thought back to primary days @wesleyhalljunior after long hours of lessons and going across to Bato so I can grab a snack. 

My entire childhood literally flashes before my eyes and made me remember the best times are enjoying the simplest things 💛

The most restful times live dearly in my heart 💜 

I love dating me!

Fun Fact: This arrangement that I used as the audio is by Dave Brubeck, Paul Desmond Joe Morello and Eugene Wright.

And how do I know this? 

Cause my dad was one of the best saxophonist in Barbados and he’d give me pop quizzes on classical musicians and their pieces.

The girls are cultured out here! Such memorable feels 🥰

Literary Arts Gala !

I ran into my first form literature teacher tonight and all the reading memories came rushing back. Our childhood activities really shape who we are when you really think about it.

Anyone who attended Foundation School in the early 2000s would remember the vast amounts of literature we had to read and my very enthusiastic yet crazy teacher kinda made me the inquisitive and also crazy person I am today through books!

Island of the blue dolphins, To Kill a Mockingbird, Escape to Last man Peak, and of course Oedipus Rex were my escapes from Foundation to UWI. 

Now I can easily reflect on the cultured childhood I had and sit in full gratitude 🩵

NIFCA RECAP! 

Wow! My November was filled with so much activity, art, love and passion! NIFCA’s 50th anniversary was definitely one to remember and I truly enjoyed every single event!

From taking Danny Dialo’s African classes, assisting Olivia’s with Gala choreography, an audience member at all the events and hosting an event, it was truly an amazing experience.

One thing I’d say is once a dancer always a dancer. Once a performer ALWAYS A PERFORMER and I thank NIFCA @thencfbarbados for that! ❤️ 

Tag a friend if you see ‘em’

PAYING ATTENTION TO DETAIL IS KEY 📌 

I work on my phones, laptops and all types of devices daily and sometimes I miss the details on what’s around me. I forget to tap into my senses of sight, hearing, feeling, smelling, tasting and that’s basically missing out on life!

This time around, I had a day at @o2beachclubbarbados to just sit down and take on EVERY SINGLE DETAIL and it’s so nice. The handcrafted rope details, the wall art, the metal structures carefully made in a leaf shape, the warm pools housed in between the pathways 🙌🏾

EVERYTHING is focused on the details and it was so refreshing to take in.

So I’ll share the amazing details @o2beachclubbarbados with you! ✨
